  "response": "The Isha Foundation is a non-profit organization founded by Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev in 1992. It is primarily known for its yoga programs, spiritual teachings, and various social and community development initiatives. The foundation operates the Isha Yoga Center in India and several centers around the world, offering programs aimed at promoting individual well-being and spiritual growth.\n\nWhile the foundation has many followers who report positive experiences, there are also critics who have raised concerns or skepticism about certain aspects of the organization. Allegations of being a \"scam\" can often arise from misunderstandings, differing beliefs, or dissatisfaction from a small number of participants.\n\nIt's important to approach such claims critically. If you\u2019re evaluating the Isha Foundation or any organization, consider researching independently, checking multiple sources, reading reviews from participants, and considering the broader context and background of any allegations or criticisms.",
